trend_summary: From earliest to latest imagery, suburban fabric matures: interchange lanes multiply, commercial roofs spread along main highways, and residential infill fills vacant lots. The southern quarry retreats and is partly reclaimed with vegetation. Overall built-up footprint grows moderately while tree cover slightly increases, sustaining medium-density suburban character.
notable_changes: Highway interchanges expanded, adding ramps and collector roads.
New warehouse and big-box rooftops appear along eastern and central corridors.
Quarry area in the south contracts and shows vegetation reclamation.
Residential infill adds cul-de-sacs and houses in northern neighborhoods.
Tree canopy and landscaped green spaces increase across the scene.
